column1: 2023-09-25T13:35:25Z,,8302869,AI,,newgraph_airvine,8302869,newgraph_airvine,,317,Gershwin Creek,Railway,,CN Rail,Closed Bottom Structure,Concrete Box,,1.5,99,"Very high value habitat upstream with pockets of gravel throughout. column1: 2023-09-26T13:00:04Z,,8800140,AI,,newgraph_airvine,8800140,newgraph_airvine,1923217,326,Tributary to Skeena River ,Highway 16,,MOTI,Closed Bottom Structure,Round Culvert,,1.5,24,"Beaver dam, approximately 1.4 m high located 5 m upstream of the inlet. Beaver influenced wetland upstream however, stream was dry at time of survey downstream of the dam. Skeena River is immediately downstream of the outlet with the high water level, approximately 2 m below pipe outlet. Culvert is in very poor condition with top side of the inlet, bent down and pipe rusted all the way through the bottom for the last 2 m of pipe at outlet. The area upstream of the highway may historically have provided refuge in high flows. However, at time of survey water levels were low with water quite stagnant. On outside bend of the Skeena, river (immediately downstream) and corner of the highway so construction may be quite difficult. column1: 2023-09-26T14:11:58Z,,8800149,AI,,newgraph_airvine,8800149,newgraph_airvine,2351,327,Tributary to Skeena River,Highway 16,,MOTI,Closed Bottom Structure,Round Culvert,,3.5,35,"Major debris accumulation downstream of the culvert. Stream is dewatered downstream for at least 60 m. There are numerous buried concrete lock blocks downstream of the outlet, which may have been part of a backwatering system. Trash rack upstream of the crossing has failed, with steel members scattered throughout the stream. There are poured concrete wing walls upstream of the crossing with the right bank being approximately 8 m long and river left bank wall at 30 m long. Bottom half of the culvert is concrete and the top half is corrugated metal. Steeper stream with step pool habitat, and bedrock throughout the channel. Dolly Varden, and cutthroat noted upstream in FISS.              Ministry of Transportation chris_hwy_structure_road_id: 2351. 14:11:58",,2023-09-26,9,539718.6960416236,6083273.506073911,No,,No,No,,4,0,1.4,No,14,10,10,No,No,Shallow Fill,Medium,,,10,,,,,,,,,,newgraph_airvine,3,1,1,5,"Strange structure, but seems to be holding up OK. River right bank has failed a string of the wing wall with large chunks of rock falling into the channel. Steel trash rock upstream has failed with steel members scattered throughout the channel. There’s a large amount of accumulated debris downstream of the outlet. Numerous concrete block blocks are located downstream with many of them buried, potentially indicating a historic  back watering Project          ",4,4,16,21," The concrete arm ring of the stream banks, upstream of the pike, likely reduce the chance of a flood event, causing a failure to the structure. Large high power stream, however, could move a lot of material to block the pipe.",10,9,2,1,10,3,35,56,"  Dolly Varden, and cutthroat noted upstream in FISS. Large amount of bedrock upstream would make construction difficult and stream. Peers unstable with large amounts of debris moving. Highway 16 so very busy expensive to work on.",20230926_142254.jpg,20230926_142307.jpg,20230926_142319.jpg,20230926_142311.jpg,20230926_142257.jpg,20230926_142314.jpg,20230926_142351.jpg,,,20230926_142356.jpg,,,,,"<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN"" ""http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd"">

column1: 2023-09-26T11:38:36Z,,8801343,AI,,newgraph_airvine,8801343,newgraph_airvine,1923189,324,Tributary to Skeena River,Highway 16,,MOTI,Closed Bottom Structure,Round Culvert,,0.6,20,"Small drainage with 1 m high beaverdam, approximately 5 m upstream of the inlet. Fine substrate. Seems unlikely that the stream is fish bearing. Historic FISS stream sample site conducted with channel dry at the time of their assessment. Culvert is in very poor condition, rusting through and bent significantly on the outlet. Pipe slope estimated as deformed pipe and position made measurement with clinometer not possible.           Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1923189. 11:38:36",,2023-09-26,9,547457.7020211625,6066323.318743889,Yes,0.2,Yes,Yes,50,1.5,0,0.25,Yes,1,1.7,1,Yes,No,Deep Fill,Low,,,10,,,,,,,,,,newgraph_airvine,4,1,2,7,Lots of beaver activity immediately upstream plus deposition of fines upstream causing blockage issues. There is some significant erosion around the inlet of the pipe as well – see photo. Outlet of pipe is severely bent and rusting right through.          ,2,3,6,13,"As there is not a lot of fill on this pipe, it seems very possible that high flow event result in water over top of the road          ",10,9,5,7,,9,,," Because of fine substrate and documentation of low flows in the past, it seems unlikely that this stream supports fish.
